<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB05590</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROVIDING FOR THE PROTECTION OF WORKERS IN THE BUSINESS PROCESS OUTSOURCING (BPO) INDUSTRY </td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Refers "Business Process Outsourcing" or "BPO" as the transfer of an organization's
non-core processes to a third-party who uses an information technology-based service
delivery, and in turn manages the selected process based on defined and measurable
performance criteria.

Seeks to protect the interests and welfare of the workers in the BPO Industry by giving them
the right to social protection that includes among others, the right to privacy of personal
calls, and for the night shift workers/employees to  have the right to stay in a
comfortable resting area within the employer's premises until daybreak to ensure their
safety.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>NOEL, FLORENCIO G.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-11-21</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON LABOR AND EMPLOYMENT ON 2019-11-27</td></tr></table>